Ahhhh... the pleasure of drunk drivers
107 posts • 123 Next
Evil_Merlin
"Oppressor of the Meek"
Ars Legatus Legionis
et Subscriptor
Tribus: Caput Mundi
Registered: Aug 9, 1999Posts: 21446
Posted: Sat Apr 07, 2012 10:13 pm
Sitting at home just about an hour ago, reading, and I hear a car come flying thru the parking lot at the condo. I was like "He is going way too fast for the parking lot". Look out the window only to see a minivan slam nose first into a tree at about 40 or so MPH. Mind you this guy was screaming thru the parking lot.Throw the shoes on really quick and grab my phone and keys. By the time I get out to the car, the kid driving is trying to get the car back into gear.I can clearly see both front airbags have deployed, and the minivan got pushed back by the collision a good 10 feet from the tree he hit. I tell the kid stay in the car and don't move, I'm calling the police and fire.Kid starts freaking out.People start showing up from other buildings in the area.Kid starts freaking out more. Then he notices I'm wearing a Plymouth County Sherriff t-shirt I am wearing and which he loses it and starts to walk away from the crash. Thankfully he is a bit too dazed to go too far.Cops show up, talk to the kid, talk to me at which time he starts to argue with the police. The police ask me to step away for a second while the kid throws a fit, trying to punch and kick the police, then he tries to spit on the police. Bad move. Police then take kid to the ground, handcuff and ankle cuff him and toss him in the back of the cruiser.Lead officer comes back over asks me a few questions. I point to the bag of drugs the kid threw out of the car as he got out of the car the first time when I walked out.Such a pleasant night...
Pysgard
