The one and only time I used OnStar emergency was when we were in traffic on 495, it was obvious the sports car in front of us had a driver falling asleep at the wheel. He kept drifting into lanes and then snapping back. The guy's head was lolling about, too. As we were reporting the make and license plate number, on the line with the operator, the car spun out, nearly hit a minivan, hit the embankment, and crashed into a grove of large trees on the side of the highway. I remembered thinking how... flimsy the car body looked. Like the guy probably hit the trees at about 20mph or less, and the hood just peeled off like it was paper. We couldn't stop, as we were in the middle lane. But we reported the wreck and the highway mile marker, and OnStar said police and ambulance had been dispatched.
