I remember the first night I was in a new apartment in a ...marginal area of San Diego, I was awoken around midnight to the sound of a man centerpunching his Jeep Cherokee right in to the telephone pole in front of my door. By the time I threw on a t-shirt and went outside to check on the occupants, I saw the driver hauling ass on foot down into the nearby canyon. I don't know how fast he was going, but the front end was completely wrapped around the pole; it took the wrecking crew a long time to sawzall it free. You could see where his head hit the windshield on the inside, too. I was amazed the driver wasn't dead, much less able to run away the way he did.-----------I'm glad you were able to keep that kid off the road. It's a lucky thing no one was injured or killed.
