I had a wreck like this in front of my house a few years ago. I was making coffee before work and wondered why the traffic was going so slowly by the house (usually, people rocket past, 20-30 miles over the speed limit). I look out the window and see a car parked across my second driveway, driver's door open, tail end sticking out into the road.I go outside and look. It was somewhat icy and the driver had lost control in front of my neighbor's house, skimmed through his drive, overcompensated, bounced off the hill across from my first driveway and came to rest in my second drive. At that point, the driver must have run away, leaving the car (still idling, with the keys in it).I called the cops and checked to make sure the guy wasn't in my back yard, under my porch or in my crawlspace. The staties got there and were... familiar with the car and the driver (which is probably why he ran in the first place).
