Evil_Merlin wrote:I clearly remember when I walked over to him and ask if he was drunk he said "Do I look drunk?" and I said "No you look like you are tweaking".His response was "The cops are going to kill me"I took a good look at the tree he hit yesterday and I'm rather surprised it isn't damaged more. Then again, it is a nice younger oak tree about 14" across.Whenever we get road trauma in, we get a bit of history from the paramedics. Rough guide: a big hardwood tree is the second-worst thing to hit. The big root ball just holds it still and the car stops very quickly. Hitting a wall is substantially better for your health.The worst is a big animal like a cow, front or rear on. Spindly legs get snapped off and you get the heavy bit through the windscreen in the face. We got a guy in like that. We stopped resuscitation when the police officer turned up just afterwards with the poor punter's brain in a carrier bag."Don't think this is any use, doc. Before or after the accident!"Police - as sick as medical humour.
